parameters: NASA recently announced they are going back to the Moon
for scientific discovery,conomic benefit, and for
inspiration for a whole new generation of explorers called
the Artemis Generation.
However, NASA has set its sights on doing more than simply
returning to the moon, they want to build a permanent
residence for humans by building homes on our lunar
neighbor.
This project has been dubbed Project Olympus. NASA has set
its aim high as they plan to have these habitable structures
on the moon by 2040 - not many years away.
NASA’s vision of establishing habitable structures represents
another giant leap for mankind.
In the meantime, the world of science news was recently abuzz
with an exciting new discovery.
A roughly Earth-sized planet orbiting the star  Proxima
Centauri was discovered and dubbed Proxima Centauri B.
It is 4.22 light years away and is in the constellation of
Centaurus. This may not sound like big news, after all we have
discovered nearly 3,000 planets.
What makes this discovery so exciting is that it is not only
similar in size to earth but that it also orbits its host star
in that star’s “Habitable Zone.”
As some of you may already know, a habitable zone means the
range of distance from a star with the right temperature for
liquid water to exist.
Think of a habitable zone as a zone or band around the star,
or the Goldilocks zone, where temperatures are just right.
Your job is to settle this planet.
